Hollow out a large wheel of @brie{8%oz} leaving a rim so it can hold the pasta; save the brie for filling.

In a #pot, bring water to a boil and cook @gnocchi{1/2%lb} until they start to float.

In a #skillet on medium heat, melt @butter{1%tbsp} and add @garlic{2%clove}; stir until fragrant, about ~{2%minutes}.

Add @heavy cream{1%cup} and stir. Then add @onion powder{1/2%tsp}, @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp}, @pepper{1/4%tsp}, and @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Add @cream cheese{2%oz}, @brie{4%oz} removed from the wheel, and @white cheddar{3/4%cup}. Mix and allow to bubble.

Add @gnocchi{1/2%lb} and stir.

Add gnocchi to your brie and wrap with puff pastry #puff pastry{1%sheet}. Coat with egg wash consisting of @egg{1%large} and @water{1%tsp}, and bake at 400Â°F until golden brown, ~{15%minutes}.